parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel rail can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or other safety hazards.

fuel mist spraying onto spark plugs
pinholes in the plastic fuel rail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge/tank unit can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to unexpected fuel exhaustion, engine stalling, or other safety issues.
symptoms: complete failure of the gas tank gauge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing accidents due to loss of power steering and brakes.
